Due to the limited amount of genetic material available in pre - <termsem="GO:0007566"> implantation </term> embryos , a nested PCR strategy was developed to yield reliable genotyping information ( Figure 4 ) .
Whole embryos were first <termsem="GO:0009056"> digested </term> in 20 L of <termsem="GO:0008233"> <termsem="independent_continuant"> proteinase </term> </term> K buffer ( see below ) .
